{
  "stem": "22869.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I had a detail of people that had a little how shall I say?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A two-wheeler, a large two-wheeler.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was in charge of it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they-- so we used to go every morning with this-- with these few guys.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember how many there were.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we used to go to the main camp, get all this bread, bring it in here, and I used to store it away.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Whoever wanted this ration would get it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But most of the guys didn't want it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what we used to do, because we were all-- because bordering the different camps is either on the way, when I-- when I came from the main camp, I would meet a detail of women or other guy-- guys who were from different camps who had no food.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We'd load them up with-- with bread, and with margarine, and with-- and soup.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sometimes our guys were eating, too, because they had no-- no way how to get something warm.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and we also had a-- a good way of becoming smugglers, you know, taking some-- some kind of valuable stuff out of the camp there and smuggle it into the main camp, and started dealing and wheeling with some other guys in the camps, you know, like bartering.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, you gave them this for that, and--",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Let's say we would take gold out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "OK, and somebody would-- in camp, being able-- there were a lot of civilians who came in, would bring in salami, kielbasa, Polish stuff.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So you would-- you would trade.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You would [INAUDIBLE] because you know, everybody in Auschwitz-- most of the stuff that they were eating from these things were cans, like, you know, like maybe tuna fish.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
